history.content: If you're planning to recruit for internships, I would suggest postponing 161 to the Spring, because both 170 and 126 are heavy classes (but 170 will help you with recruiting, will prep you well for interview questions).

history.content:
For this upcoming fall semester, I plan to take CS 170, EE 126, and CS 161. In terms of the workload, is this a manageable schedule? If it is not, which class should I drop, and what upper division CS class that is light in workload could I switch it with?

For reference: 

  • I am a rising junior EECS major. 
  • I have completed all of my lower division CS, EE, math, and physics courses.
  • I have completed all of my HSS breadth requirements. 
  • My extracurricular commitments (as of now) are relatively light (~5-7 hours/week). 
  • My career interests are in machine learning and artificial intelligence, so that is why I want to take EE 126.
  • I am planning to recruit for internships in the fall.

Thank you very much!!
